cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for weakly supervised anomaly detection, which involves both labeled and unlabeled data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these, machine learning and computer vision are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing a neural network-based approach for anomaly detection.
